description:
MongoDB 4.4 introduces a new "provenance" field to write concern errors, which describes the origin of the write concern associated with the error. For example:
{code}"writeConcernError" : {
    "code" : 64,
    "codeName" : "WriteConcernFailed",
    "errmsg" : "waiting for replication timed out",
    "errInfo" : {
        "wtimeout" : true,
        "writeConcern" : {
            "w" : 2,
            "wtimeout" : 1000,
            "provenance" : "clientSupplied"
        }
    }
}
{code}
Though drivers should not parse the "errInfo" field of a writeConcernError, drivers must ensure that the provenance field is accessible to users so that developers/admins can be aware of situations such as custom write concern defaults causing wtimeouts, etc.

SPEC-1578 makes explicit how a WriteConcernError should be constructed from a server reply. Drivers need to validate (or update if necessary) the logic for constructing WriteConcernError,  and implement a new prose test to validate a "provenance" is accessible from a WriteConcernError.

Spec change: https://github.com/mongodb/specifications/commit/7745234f93039a83ae42589a6c0cdbefcffa32fa

The [server selection spec|https://github.com/mongodb/specifications/blob/9465cda31270e41d3d87fe9b9b14ad601c3861c6/source/server-selection/server-selection.rst#topology-type-single] states the following for topology type single (which means either a deployment of one server or any deployment with a direct connection to a server in the deployment):
{quote}
... The single server is always suitable for reads if it is available ...
... The single server is always suitable for write operations if it is available.
{quote}
Additionally, the [SDAM spec|https://github.com/mongodb/specifications/blob/9465cda31270e41d3d87fe9b9b14ad601c3861c6/source/server-discovery-and-monitoring/server-discovery-and-monitoring.rst#general-requirements] requires:
{quote}
A client MUST be able to connect to a single server of any type. This includes querying hidden replica set members, and connecting to uninitialized members ...
{quote}
However, the [SDAM spec|https://github.com/stIncMale/specifications/blob/ff282c752dc73ae49622df4ac87a68a9e9dbe95c/source/server-discovery-and-monitoring/server-discovery-and-monitoring.rst#connection-pool-management] requires to create and mark as ready only pools for data-bearing servers:
{quote}
... if the server is determined to be data-bearing and does not already have a connection pool, the driver MUST create the connection pool for the server. Additionally, if a driver implements a CMAP compliant connection pool, the server's pool (even if it already existed) MUST be marked as "ready".
{quote}
It is also reflected in the [corresponding SDAM pseudocode|https://github.com/stIncMale/specifications/blob/ff282c752dc73ae49622df4ac87a68a9e9dbe95c/source/server-discovery-and-monitoring/server-discovery-and-monitoring.rst#replacing-the-topologydescription]:
{code}
# for drivers that implement CMAP, mark the connection pool as ready after
# a successful check on a data bearing server.
if server.type in (Mongos, RSPrimary, RSSecondary, Standalone, LoadBalanced):
    pool.ready()
{code}
The above means that in case of a direct connection to a non-[data-bearing|https://github.com/stIncMale/specifications/blob/ff282c752dc73ae49622df4ac87a68a9e9dbe95c/source/server-discovery-and-monitoring/server-discovery-and-monitoring.rst#data-bearing-server-type] [server type|https://github.com/mongodb/specifications/blob/9465cda31270e41d3d87fe9b9b14ad601c3861c6/source/server-discovery-and-monitoring/server-discovery-and-monitoring.rst#servertype] (e.g., {{RSArbiter}}), the server can be selected, but it does not have a connection pool and, therefore, is unusable.

It appears that we need to change the wording to
{quote}
... if the server is determined to be [data-bearing|https://github.com/mongodb/specifications/blob/9465cda31270e41d3d87fe9b9b14ad601c3861c6/source/server-discovery-and-monitoring/server-discovery-and-monitoring.rst#data-bearing-server-type] or a [direct connection|https://github.com/mongodb/specifications/blob/9465cda31270e41d3d87fe9b9b14ad601c3861c6/source/server-discovery-and-monitoring/server-discovery-and-monitoring.rst#general-requirements] to the server is requested, and does not already have a connection pool, the driver MUST create the connection pool for the server. Additionally, if a driver implements a CMAP compliant connection pool, the server's pool (even if it already existed) MUST be marked as "ready".
{quote}
and the pseudocode to
{code}
# for drivers that implement CMAP, mark the connection pool as ready after a successful check
if (server.type in (Mongos, RSPrimary, RSSecondary, Standalone, LoadBalanced))
        or (server.type != Unknown and newTopologyDescription.type == Single):
    pool.ready()
{code}

